label: Receipt book
attribution: Provided by the University of Pennsylvania Libraries.

metadata.label: Description
value: A collection of over 100 recipes, arranged in loose order of fruit recipes (including preserving, fruit pastes, dried fruit, and candying); pickling recipes for vegetables, beans, shellfish, and fish; potted and collared meats; cakes, puddings, balls (dumplings), and cheesecakes; meat jellies; puff and shortcrust pastry; meat recipes (including brisk of mutton, bumbard of veal, leg of mutton a la mode); fish recipes (including roast pike and boiled cod's head); salted meats; boiled savory puddings; sweet puddings; wines, condiments, and sauces (Alastor).  The second quire (f. 25-32) and back wrapper are both detached.  A list of recipes at the end (f. 32r-32v) is a table of contents, sometimes diverging from the order in the manuscript, for the first half of the volume (f. 1r-15v).

metadata.label: Extent
value: 32 leaves : paper ; 200 x 160 mm bound to 200 x 160 mm.

metadata.label: Note
value: Foliation:  Paper, 32 leaves; [1-32], modern foliation in pencil, lower right recto; a leaf has been torn out after f. 15, with no apparent loss of text, and the foliation does not include the missing leaf.

Binding:  Original (18th-century) paper wrappers, with back wrapper detached and lacking upper quarter and front wrapper printed with an engraved portrait medallion of Leopold I, Holy Roman Emperor (1640-1705), with a decorative border and touches of hand coloring (Alastor).
Origin: Probably written in England (pen trials on back wrapper include the words London and Yarmouth), circa 1739 (Richard Holme inscription inside front wrapper).
Acquired for the Penn Libraries with assistance from the Edgar Fahs Smith Memorial Fund.

metadata.label: Relation
value: The Edgar Fahs Smith Memorial Fund Home Page: http://hdl.library.upenn.edu/1017.12/366281

metadata.label: Physical Location
value: Kislak Center for Special Collections, Rare Books and Manuscripts, Manuscripts, Ms. Codex 2096

metadata.label: Provenance
value: Early reader inscriptions include the names of Robert Thornten (front wrapper), Ann Taylor (f. 32v, dated December 25th 1778), and Ann Williamson (f. 32v, dated 1785, and back wrapper)
Sold by Alastor Rare Books Ltd. (East Cowes, England), 2022.
